<div style="text-align: center; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; background: rgba(51, 51, 51,.8); padding: 10px; color:white">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>The 4 Quadrants of Tasks</h1>
        <p>Welcome to our homepage discussing the 4 quadrants of tasks as outlined in "The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People" by Stephen Covey. Understanding these quadrants can fundamentally change the way we approach our daily activities and responsibilities. By categorizing tasks based on urgency and importance, individuals can prioritize effectively, increase productivity, and achieve a greater sense of balance and fulfillment in both personal and professional domains.</p>
        <hr>
        <div class="quadrants">
            <div class="quadrant">
                <h2>Quadrant I: Urgent and Important</h2>
                <p>Tasks in this quadrant are both urgent and important. They require immediate attention and often involve crises or deadlines.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="quadrant">
                <h2>Quadrant II: Not Urgent but Important</h2>
                <p>Tasks in this quadrant are important for long-term goals and personal development. They require proactive planning and focus.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="quadrant">
                <h2>Quadrant III: Urgent but Not Important</h2>
                <p>Tasks in this quadrant are urgent but may not contribute significantly to long-term goals. They often involve distractions and interruptions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="quadrant">
                <h2>Quadrant IV: Not Urgent and Not Important</h2>
                <p>Tasks in this quadrant are neither urgent nor important. They are often time-wasters and distractions that should be minimized.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>